# The val-name macro must produce the ids coreJVM / coreJS / coreNative and appJVM / ... .
# Compiling each of these (referenced by id) proves the macro derived ids from the `val` names,
# that CrossType.Pure picked up shared + platform-specific sources, and that the cross dependsOn
# wired app -> core on every platform. (Native only compiles to NIR; no clang toolchain needed.)
> coreJVM/compile
> coreJS/compile
> coreNative/compile

# The per-platform jvmSettings / jsSettings / nativeSettings must each reach only their platform.
> checkVersions

# Shared test sources (<base>/src/test/scala) must be on the Test source path.
> coreJVM/Test/compile

> appJVM/compile
> appJS/compile
> appNative/compile

# Run the JVM app: the assertion inside fails the build unless the shared (Shared), per-platform
# (Platform), and cross-version (Versioned, in src/main/scala-3) sources all resolve at runtime.
> appJVM/run
$ exists app-ran.txt
